This paper discusses algorithms for style transfer, which involves manipulating visual content. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses real-time style transfer, which involves optimizing algorithms for speed, and this could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
